      • buildSlots

        private static ObjectSlot[] buildSlots(ObjectStreamField[] fields)
        Build emulated slots that correspond to emulated fields. A slot is a field descriptor (ObjectStreamField) plus the actual value it holds.
        Parameters:
        fields - an array of ObjectStreamField, which describe the fields to be emulated (names, types, etc).

      • defaulted

        public boolean defaulted(String name)
                  throws IllegalArgumentException
        Returns true indicating the field called name has not had a value explicitly assigned and that it still holds a default value for its type, or false indicating that the field named has been assigned a value explicitly.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the field to test.
        Returns:
        true if name still holds its default value, false otherwise
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if name is null

      • findSlot

        private ObjectSlot findSlot(String fieldName,
                            Class<?> fieldType)
        Finds and returns an ObjectSlot that corresponds to a field named fieldName and type fieldType. If the field type fieldType corresponds to a primitive type, the field type has to match exactly or null is returned. If the field type fieldType corresponds to an object type, the field type has to be compatible in terms of assignment, or null is returned. If fieldType is null, no such compatibility checking is performed and the slot is returned.
        Parameters:
        fieldName - the name of the field to find
        fieldType - the type of the field. This will be used to test compatibility. If null, no testing is done, the corresponding slot is returned.
        Returns:
        the object slot, or null if there is no field with that name, or no compatible field (relative to fieldType)
